						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Rājēndra I Year 3: 1015 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Incomplete and damaged. Seems to refer to the death of a certain Śrutimāṉ Nakkaṉ Chandiraṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Rājamalla Muttaraiyaṉ, a resident of Tiruvūrattūr in [Ūṟ]ṟattūr-nāḍu (a sub-division) of Viḻā-nāḍu. He was ordered by the king <hi rend="italic">(perumāḷ tiruvāy-moḻiya)</hi> to attack Satayāśraya [the western Chālukya king ?] and to pierce the latter's elephant. This soldier apparently lost his life in the encounter, a gift was made for his merit to the temple of Mahādēva at Tiruvūṟṟattūr. </p>						

						</summary>
